section.section:
Rules adopted in accordance with this subsection shall:
provide for the content of the seminar required under this section;
require successful completion of the seminar by all parties to the action within a certain time after the service of the original complaint upon the defendant;
establish sanctions for failure to successfully complete the seminar required under this section;
for purposes of funding the cost of the seminar, establish a fee that:
shall be assessed as costs; and
may be waived under appropriate circumstances; and
establish criteria for exemption from the requirement that the parties participate in an educational seminar, except that a court may not exempt the parties from attending the educational seminar if there is any evidence of domestic violence or child abuse or neglect.
